dcterms:creator: M. Vickers
S. Chan
dcterms:description: The Vickers-Chan dataset represents the social structure of students from a school in Victoria, Australia. Each node represents a student studying in 7th grade, and the three graph layers are constructed based on student responses for three questions.
dcterms:title: Vickers-Chan

dcterms:creator: Jeffrey Curtis Schlimmer
dcterms:description: The Congress votes dataset is obtained from the 1984 United States Congressional Voting Records Database. This includes votes from every congressman on 16 different bills, resulting in a 16-layered graph.
dcterms:title: Congress Votes

dcterms:creator: Pin-Yu Chen
Alfred O Hero
dcterms:description: This dataset is a temporal collaboration network of professors Jure Leskovec and Andrew Ng, partitioned into 5-year intervals to build a 4-layered graph based on co-authorship.
dcterms:title: Leskovec-Ng

dcterms:creator: James Coleman
Elihu Katz
Herbert Menzel
dcterms:description: The Reinnovation dataset describes the Global Innovation Index for 144 countries, with labels representing the development level of each country across 12 sectors.
dcterms:title: Reinnovation

dcterms:creator: Dheeru Dua
Casey Graff
dcterms:description: This dataset contains information about mammographic mass lesions from 961 subjects, with various attributes used to construct layers of the graph.
dcterms:title: Mammography (UCI)

dcterms:creator: James Coleman
Elihu Katz
Herbert Menzel
dcterms:description: The CKM dataset models information diffusion through social networks among physicians, with three layers encoding similarity in responses to a questionnaire.
dcterms:title: CKM

dcterms:creator: Dheeru Dua
Casey Graff
dcterms:description: The Balance Scale dataset summarizes results from a psychological experiment, using attributes to construct a 4-layered graph.
dcterms:title: Balance Scale
